\par\par \b \uc2  Economists say state  \highlight22\uc2 budget \highlight\uc2  too optimistic. \b0\par\par\uc2 1,269 \uc2 words\par \uc2 7 January 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The 32.1 percent increase in the 1998/1999 draft state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  unveiled by President Soeharto last night is unrealistic in the current \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation, according to economists. \par \par \uc2  "It is overly optimistic and is almost wishful thinking," Indonesian Business Data Center chairman Christianto Wibisono said yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Economist Bomer Pasaribu and market analyst David Chang shared Christianto's view that the draft \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  showed too much optimism amid the monetary crisis. \par \par \uc2  "It's too brave and it will require very hard work," Pasaribu said. \par \par \uc2  Chang said such optimism did not seem to go in line with the expectation of the people in the financial and capital markets. \par \par \uc2  "I think it's just a bit higher than markets expected previously," Chang, the head of research at Trimegah Securities, said. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  calls for next year's \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  to equal revenue at Rp 133.5 trillion ($33.4 billion at the exchange rate of Rp 4,000 to the dollar) in \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year 1998/1999, up from Rp 101.1 trillion this year. \par \par \uc2  The financial and capital markets previously expected the government to launch a much more conservative \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  in \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  1998/1999 to cope with the monetary crisis that has hampered the country over the past few months. \par \par \uc2  Chang said the figures in oil revenues seemed reasonable, but non-oil revenues were not. \par \par \uc2  This showed that the Indonesian government did not maintain a tight \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which would eventually damage the disbursement of the IMF-led financial package in helping the country's ailing \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , he said. \par \par \uc2  "The IMF wants Indonesia to have a \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  surplus," he said. \par \par \uc2  Director of the Institute for Development of Economics and Finance Didik Rachbini said there was \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "\b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  regarding the draft state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  is even more than in previous years in a situation like this," he told The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2  Didik said the two components which remained \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the draft \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  were oil and gas revenues and revenue from foreign loans. \par \par \uc2  The government estimates its revenues from oil and gas will rise 83.5 percent. \par \par \uc2  The estimate was based on the price of crude oil at US$17 per barrel and with the exchange rate set at Rp 4,000 against the dollar, he said. \par \par \uc2  Yesterday, the rupiah continued to decline to almost 8,000 against the greenback. \par \par \uc2  He said \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  for loan repayments rose 57 percent because of the dollar's sharp rise in value and also because of the large amount of the loans. \par \par \uc2  "A third of our \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  is to repay loans, he said, and this will reduce \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  in development," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said the government's role in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was to finance the development of smaller areas and informal sectors to eliminate poverty. \par \par \uc2  However, half the amount of \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  would go toward routine \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , such as salaries and loan repayments, instead of development, he said. \par \par \uc2  Responding to the remarks made by Minister of Finance Mar'ie Muhammad that the government would make an effort to create a 1 percent surplus in the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Didik questioned where the surplus would come from. \par \par \uc2  "They cannot lift the fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to have a surplus in the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . It's too hard. It must be done when the situation returns to normal," he said. \par \par \uc2  Pasaribu, the chairman of the Center for Labor and Development Studies, said the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  was stagnant. \par \par \uc2  Pasaribu said the slight expansion in the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  was too small to have a significant impact. \par \par \uc2  The flat \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  would result in a scarcity of jobs this year, he said. \par \par \uc2  "Even with an optimistic projection, the level of unemployment would continue to rise this year," he said. \par \par \uc2  He predicted unemployment would rise by over 11 percent, including those who worked less than an hour per day. \par \par \uc2  The percentage of unemployed, including disguised unemployment, would be about 51 percent this year, up from 45 percent last year, he said. \par \par \uc2  According to the Central Bureau of Statistics, the unemployed made up 38 percent of the total population in 1996. \par \par \uc2  Last year, about 40 million people were unemployed, of which 8.9 million worked less than an hour per week, he said. \par \par \uc2  He estimated the unemployed would total about 47 million people this year. \par \par \uc2  This meant out of the 200 million people in the country, only 44 million would be productive, he said. \par \par \uc2  "One person will have to support an average of 4.5 people," he said. \par \par \uc2  Christianto said the government's estimate, on which the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  was based and the rupiah's value kept at 4,000 against the U.S. dollar, was also overconfident. \par \par \uc2  "The regional fever is not over yet. In the midst of this optimism, the rupiah continues to plunge," he said. (aly/das/rid) \par \par \uc2  Table: 1997-98 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and draft 1998-99 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  (Rp billion) \par \par \uc2  REVENUES 1997-98 1998-99 % change \par \par \uc2  - \par \par \uc2  A. DOMESTIC REVENUES 88,060.7 107,687.9 22.3 \par \par \uc2  I. Oil and natural gas 14,871.1 27,286.4 83.5 \par \par \uc2  1. Oil 10,688.2 18,869.7 76.5 \par \par \uc2  2. Natural gas 4,182.9 8,416.7 101.2 \par \par \uc2  II. Non-oil and non-gas 73,189.6 80,401.5 9.9 \par \par \uc2  1. Income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  29,117.7 26.337.0 -9.5 \par \par \uc2  2. Value added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  24,601.4 27,830.0 13.1 \par \par \uc2  3. Import duties 3,321.7 3,179.8 -4.3 \par \par \uc2  4. Excise \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  4,436.3 4,649.6 4.8 \par \par \uc2  5. Export \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  100.0 110.0 10.0 \par \par \uc2  6. Property \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  2,505.0 3,411.0 36.2 \par \par \uc2  7. Other \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  632.5 540.0 -14.6 \par \par \uc2  8. Non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  receipts 8,225.8 14,344.1 74.4 \par \par \uc2  9. Fuel sales profit 249.2 0.0 -100.0 \par \par \uc2  B. DEVELOPMENT REVENUES 13,026.0 25,804.0 98.1 \par \par \uc2  I. Program aid - 6,800.0 0.0 