\par\par \b \uc2  PHRI predicts gloomy year for tourism. \b0\par\par\uc2 481 \uc2 words\par \uc2 10 January 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Indonesian tourism may suffer again this year from the political impact of the upcoming presidential election in March, the chairman of the Indonesian Hotel and Restaurant Association (PHRI), Pontjo Sutowo, has said. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the presidential election during the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) meeting in March might make prospective tourists cancel or delay their trips to come here for fear of social unrest, Pontjo said Thursday. \par \par \uc2  Members of MPR, mostly made up of members of the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 , will elect a new president and approve the State \b \highlight22\uc2 Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Guidelines during the March meeting. The dominant Golkar political faction said it would support the reelection of Soeharto, which has ruled the country for three decades. \par \par \uc2  "Social unrest is the worse enemy of tourism," Pontjo said after the association's breaking of the fast ceremony. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  turmoil which had hit several Asian countries, dropping the value of their currencies, would also continue to contribute to the dismal prospects of tourism, at least in the first half of this year, he said. \par \par \uc2  Last year, the growth in the number of foreign tourist arrivals fell to its lowest level in a decade due partly to the haze problem, which blanketed most parts of Kalimantan and Sumatra in the second half of last year, and sporadic riots ahead of the general election in May. \par \par \uc2  Tourists from Asia made up 40 percent of all foreign tourist arrivals, he said. \par \par \uc2  Pontjo said many star-rated hotels had suffered more from the crisis than non-star hotels. \par \par \uc2  Star-rated hotels, which charged in U.S. dollars, had already lost their domestic market, he said. \par \par \uc2  He did not say how far occupancy rates had dropped during the monetary crisis, which has seen the rupiah's value fall 75 percent against the dollar. \par \par \uc2  However, non-star hotels have been benefiting from the crisis, he said. \par \par \uc2  These hotels, which charged their customers in rupiah, had grabbed the domestic market, he said. \par \par \uc2  Pontjo said the Indonesian hotel industry must adjust to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  turmoil in order to lure visitors from the region again. \par \par \uc2  "One way of doing it is by using the Asian currency basket," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said the exchange rate should be adjusted to the average of the Asian currencies to the U.S. dollar. \par \par \uc2  The measure could be done with the cooperation of other countries in the region, he said. The measure could use instruments such as vouchers. \par \par \uc2  "If we do not adjust to the decrease (of arrivals) from Asian countries, our market could be grabbed by other countries in the region which are more competitive than us," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said the measure could make inter-Asian traveling similar to domestic traveling. \par \par \uc2  "We can persuade Malaysians who cannot afford to go to London, for example, to go to Indonesia instead," he said. (das) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du1a007ad\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
