\par\par \b \uc2  Food producers warned not to cut supply stocks. \b0\par\par\uc2 598 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 January 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Minister of Trade and Industry Tunky Ariwibowo warned food producers Saturday not to hoard stocks and cut supply to the local market. \par \par \uc2  The minister said that such an irresponsible act would not only worsen the already panicked market but could also destabilize the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "This practice is irresponsible, I urged these companies to stop it and supply the domestic market immediately," he said after a meeting Saturday with food producers. \par \par \uc2  Tunky was referring to reports that some producers of food products and other essentials were withholding their products to benefit from the panic buying at stores and supermarkets. \par \par \uc2  But he did not give a concrete sanction to be imposed on those who were found intentionally building stocks to benefit from the price increases. \par \par \uc2  "We'll wait and see if they abide by this appeal. If not, we'll find a more effective measure," he said. \par \par \uc2  "But I urged these companies to disregard the short-term profits and instead, consider the long-term benefits." \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  rushed to supermarkets and other grocery stores to buy essentials such as rice, cooking oil and milk on fears of price increases following the sharp drop in the rupiah to Rp 10,000 against the U.S. dollar on Thursday afternoon. Several supermarkets had to close their stores early because they could not cope with the crowds of shoppers. \par \par \uc2  As panic buying continued Saturday in shopping centers in the country's major cities, Tunky called for the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  to be calm because the government has taken steps to guarantee the supply of food. \par \par \uc2  "During a hardship like what we're facing now, we need togetherness and to share our burden," he added. \par \par \uc2  Tunky said food companies complained during the meeting that the turmoil had doubly burdened them. \par \par \uc2  He said the companies claimed they could not set the prices because of sharp fluctuations of the rupiah against the dollar. \par \par \uc2  The dollar's sharp appreciation on the rupiah by over 300 percent since early July has inflated the prices of imported materials. \par \par \uc2  At the same time, the flow of local materials had not been smooth because their suppliers faced the same problems, he said. \par \par \uc2  But if the companies continued to withhold their products, there would be a shortage in the supply, he said, adding that prices would surge drastically, making the products unaffordable for consumers. \par \par \uc2  In turn, the producers could suffer losses from lower sales, while they also had to bear high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , he said. \par \par \uc2  Tunky said the producers had asked the government to help ease some of their burdens during the turmoil. \par \par \uc2  He said they asked that customs fees to be reduced, and to eliminate the luxury \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  on some food products. \par \par \uc2  "It is a bit curious that food products are imposed with a luxury \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  when food is an essential need of the people," he remarked. \par \par \uc2  He said the producers also asked the government to reevaluate other duties imposed on import activities. \par \par \uc2  Tunky said he would discuss the matter with Minister of Finance Mar'ie Muhammad. \par \par \uc2  He said he would also meet soon with the producers of food supporting industries of paper, plastic and cans. \par \par \uc2  Tunky said the food producers reported that their productions remain normal and that there had been no production cut. \par \par \uc2  "Factories are still operating three shifts. The only thing they were concern with was the price \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said representatives of the producers and the ministry's senior staff had begun working Saturday on determining stable prices for their products. (das) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du1c007c6\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
