\par\par \b \uc2  Amien, Gus Dur back Megawati's presidency bid. \b0\par\par\uc2 680 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 January 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Two prominent government critics supported yesterday Megawati Soekarnoputri's bid for presidency, lauding the bold move as a boost for democratization. \par \par \uc2  Moslem scholars Amien Rais and Abdurrahman Wahid, however, tempered their appreciation by expressing doubt that the declaration of the ousted leader of the Indonesian Democratic Party (PDI) would cause more than just a ripple in real politics, given that Megawati was actually residing out of the "system". \par \par \uc2  Chairman of the dominant Golkar Harmoko said in Tulungagung, East Java, that everybody could have a bid at presidency, but it should be done through proper mechanisms. He was also quoted by Antara as saying yesterday that people could not just name themselves presidential candidates "out of the blue". \par \par \uc2  "Megawati has only a slight chance as she fights for the presidency from outside the system," said Amien Rais, who leads the 28 million-strong Muhammadiyah Moslem organization and who was recently named a presidential candidate by a branch of the United Development Party (PPP). \par \par \uc2  "It is almost impossible as the government always refers (the presidential succession) to the People's Consultative Assembly's mechanism," Amien said. \par \par \uc2  Abdurrahman, better known as Gus Dur, agreed. \par \par \uc2  "It (Megawati's declaration of willingness to be president) will affect political life here, although (the effect) will not be as great as some people would expect," Abdurrahman said. \par \par \uc2  "(The bid) is almost impossible to materialize as it is not made through the system." \par \par \uc2  Abdurrahman said millions of people here still depended on the prevailing political system for reform rather than on opposition parties. \par \par \uc2  Megawati, the eldest daughter of Indonesia's first president Sukarno, declared her readiness to become a presidential candidate Saturday and urged incumbent President Soeharto not to run for a seventh consecutive term. \par \par \uc2  "With all sincerity and honesty ... I will be ready to lead this country if it is the wish and aspiration of the people," she said at a ceremony commemorating the PDI's 25th anniversary. \par \par \uc2  Amien said Megawati's declaration was a greatly needed breakthrough for Indonesia. Few political figures have dared to step forward and name themselves presidential candidates. \par \par \uc2  Amien himself, after making countless demands for succession, said he "dared" to become president should he be nominated. \par \par \uc2  Amien also supported Megawati's call for Soeharto not to seek another term. \par \par \uc2  "It is time Soeharto stepped down as (this is) a prerequisite to overcome the present multidimensional crisis," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said it was also time the government encouraged several leading political figures to nominate or be nominated as presidential candidates. \par \par \uc2  "If the government allows this, at least half a dozen people will come out and (declare their readiness to) replace Soeharto," Amien said. \par \par \uc2  Megawati cited Saturday names like Vice President Try Sutrisno, Minister of Information R. Hartono, Army Chief of Staff Gen. Wiranto, State Minister of Research and Technology B.J. Habibie, State Minister of National Development Planning Ginandjar Kartasasmita, former vice president Sudharmono and former minister of home affairs Rudini as people who have often been lauded as possible candidates. \par \par \uc2  Abdurrahman said the country's current political situation was \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  and subject to social unrest. \par \par \uc2  "The system of national succession is \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  ... we do not know how it works," Abdurrahman said, referring to the government's lack of transparency in its efforts to cope with the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. \par \par \uc2  "\b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 ' members should summon the government to explain the crisis, but unfortunately they are not willing to do this." \par \par \uc2  He said \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political reforms were necessary, but it would be some time before they can be carried out. \par \par \uc2  "Something inside our political system must be fixed first," he said. \par \par \uc2  He warned that people's anger was building up all the time and may reach a critical stage in three or four years when they will "take action". \par \par \uc2  He said people would resort to violence if "the government does not deliver what the people need". \par \par \uc2  He called on the government to show political maturity in dealing with the mounting \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  pressure for political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform. (10) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du1c007cb\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Indonesian shares rebound in New York. \b0\par\par\uc2 403 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 January 1998\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Indonesian shares listed on the New York bourse - through American depository receipt (ADR) - came under a buying spree in the wake of US President Bill Clinton's and the IMF's teams' planned visits to Jakarta with the aim of dealing with the monetary crisis. \par \par \uc2  "Indonesian shares rebounded when the rupiah strengtehend against the dollar to about 8,000, after opening at 10,225," said a broker in New York's bourse, as quoted by Dow Jones. \par \par \uc2  Telkom shares closed at 7/8 cents higher at US$6 9/16 cents at 15.53 GMT, after falling 40% in the previous session. Indosat shares also strengthened 1/16 cents to US$11 7/16 cents. \par \par \uc2  The situation on the JSX this week is predicted to remain stagnant because of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the money market. \par \par \uc2  Analysts doubt that last week's rupiah rebound reflects the real condition of the rupiah as at the time almost all currencies in the region also weakened while its bourses slowed. \par \par \uc2  "The rise in the dollar, which hit the 10,000 mark, and the drastic drop within a day cannot be explained in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2 , but political terms," said an analyst. \par \par \uc2  "In general, foreigners did more selling than buying last week, in a way that brought about corrections to the capital market," he said. \par \par \uc2  The JSX Composite Index last week stood corrected by 16.35% (67.041 points) and closed at 342.970. \par \par \uc2  2.319 millions shares changed hands, valued at Rp 2.549 trillion. \par \par \uc2  Foreign investors made a net gain of Rp 75.304 billion from selling Rp 1,504.246 billion and buying Rp 1,428.942 worth of shares. As such, the market capitalization figures last week stood at Rp 140.301 trillion. \par \par \uc2  Telkom, Indah Kiat Pulp & Paper, Indosat, HM Sampoerna, Gudang Garam, Astra International, Medco Energi, BNI 1946 and Bimantara Citra were among the prime shares in which investors were interested. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, efforts by the share rating body, PT Pefindo, to re-assess the ranking of 51 \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  companies would have little impact on share trading, \par \par \uc2  Sri Adiningsih, a consultant and a lecturer at University of Indonesia, said, reasoning that investors are already aware that the fundamentals and performances of companies have been affected by the monetary crisis. \par \par \uc2  PT Pefindo recently designated 'red alert' status to 51 companies in 11 industrial sectors. (06/rr/amu). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010922du1c0001v\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
