\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Economic \highlight\uc2 , political reforms must work together. \b0\par\par\uc2 399 \uc2 words\par \uc2 13 January 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms made to deal with the lingering \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis will only succeed if they are coupled with democratic political reforms which ensure the enforcement of law, the National Commission on Human Rights said here yesterday. \par \par \uc2  In a biting three-page statement, the commission censured the government's failure to resolve fundamental political problems which have aggravated the current crisis. \par \par \uc2  These problems include an impotent democracy which has failed to empower the people and install checks on the government, and the crippling of law enforcement which is unresponsive to the people's needs and rampant social injustices. \par \par \uc2  "The democratic, legal and social ambiguities are caused by the disabling of institutions such as the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 , law enforcement and other social control apparatus," the commission's secretary-general Baharuddin Lopa said, reading from the statement. \par \par \uc2  He said the situation was compounded by rampant and widely practiced corruption and collusion. \par \par \uc2  "The National Commission on Human Rights realizes that these problems have hampered the creation of a conducive climate toward the advancement and protection of human rights," Lopa said. \par \par \uc2  Another commission member, Marzuki Darusman, said these underlying problems were unresolved. \par \par \uc2  "These problems have accumulated as the government has never made a serious attempt to handle them," he said. \par \par \uc2  Lopa, however, said the commission understood that resolving such long term problems was difficult especially when faced with a monetary crisis such as now. \par \par \uc2  He urged that \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political reform be conducted in unison. \par \par \uc2  The commission urged government and military officials to be more prudent in making \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  statements so as to avoid creating \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  confusion, uneasiness and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "Officials should make transparent, honest and consistent statements," he said. \par \par \uc2  Lopa said the government should also start a national movement to curb private sector debts which are widely believed to be one of the causes of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. \par \par \uc2  He said the government should implement labor intensive programs immediately to reduce the rising tide of unemployment. \par \par \uc2  The commission further urged the government to establish an emergency social fund to subsidize the millions of people who have lost their jobs. \par \par \uc2  The number of unemployed this year is expected to reach 5.8 million. \par \par \uc2  The commission also said the government appeared to react sluggishly and lack coordination when dealing with its many problems such as social unrest, famine and forest fires. (10) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du1d007de\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
