\par\par \b \uc2  Causes of the crisis. \b0\par\par\uc2 368 \uc2 words\par \uc2 27 January 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  4 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Now that Indonesia is experiencing an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  meltdown, it may be more than instructive to look at what caused it. \par \par \uc2  Unlike the IMF, I do not think poor \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary policies and market imperfections were the prime causes. Rather, the origins of the present crisis lie much deeper, in the very fabric of Indonesian society. \par \par \uc2  First, there has been a failure to integrate and obtain the loyalty of the economically powerful ethnic Chinese community, thus increasing the country's vulnerability to capital flight. Huge disparities of wealth have left vast amounts of surplus capital in the hands of a few and, thus, have also increased the possibility of capital flight. \par \par \uc2  Second, many of the country's banks are amateurish with patronizing and bureaucratic attitudes irresponsive to the needs of competitive business. \par \par \uc2  Third, there has been an emphasis on the notional rather than the actual, on semblance rather than substance, in education, business, society, politics, law, religion etc. \par \par \uc2  Fourth, there has been a level of optimism and consumerism disproportionate to the productivity of Indonesia's human resources leading to massive short-term borrowing overseas. \par \par \uc2  Fifth, there has been tremendous \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  regarding the presidential succession and the possibility of a tumultuous handover of power. \par \par \uc2  Thus, unlike those in Mexico and Argentina before it, Indonesia's problems are deep-seated and will not respond merely to \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  tinkering. Unless a clear-sighted approach is applied to deal with the above problems, confidence in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will continue to plummet. The resulting black hole created may cause huge shock waves across the globe. \par \par \uc2  Having enjoyed the spoils of Indonesia's now rapidly evaporating \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  success, the West would be foolish to do little more than offer palliatives. The way the West handles this crisis will be crucial, not only to its own economies but also to the way it is seen in the Islamic world and the developing world for years to come. What is required is unequivocable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and moral support on a massive scale, allowing Indonesia the time it needs to make essential, profound and difficult adjustments amounting to a veritable revolution that could otherwise turn violent. \par \par \uc2  FRANK RICHARDSON \par \par \uc2  Jakarta \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du1r00axu\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
