so sceptical over the ability of the private sector to service its debts after the government announced that it would not bail out troubled companies. \par \par \uc2  The private sector's debts account for 70% of the GDP in terms of the present exchange rate of the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  Duff & Phelps has maintained that debt obligations on the part of the government remain solid as the IMF has pledged financial assistance amounting to US$43 billion. (ind). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010922du2e0007b\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
