\par\par \b \uc2  Pawnshop loans drop drastically. \b0\par\par\uc2 363 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 February 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  3 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Monthly loans issued by the city's 23 state-run pawnshops dropped last month by 11.76 percent to Rp 30 billion (US$3.16 million), the first such plunge in many years. \par \par \uc2  City Pawnshop Office spokesman Soeparto told The Jakarta Post that the significant post-Idul Fitri holiday drop was amazing. \par \par \uc2  "Normally, we lend a great amount of money after the Idul Fitri holiday because there are crowds of people flocking pawnshops to ask for cash to start businesses or fund their daily living after they had spent most of their money during the holiday," he said. \par \par \uc2  The sluggish demand for pawnshop loans last month is being put down to many people no longer having belongings to mortgage as security for loans in the current \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  turmoil. \par \par \uc2  "This weak condition could lasted the whole year," Soeparto predicted. \par \par \uc2  January's significant plunge was the first drop since the rupiah began to collapse in July. \par \par \uc2  "In December, for instance, we distributed loans totaling around Rp 34 billion," Soeparto said. \par \par \uc2  He said many pawnshop clients did not dare borrow money from banks because many of the latter were also ailing on account of the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  fluctuation of the rupiah which has caused the current financial difficulties and prices of basic goods to soar. \par \par \uc2  In addition to loan requests declining, pawnshops are also facing another problem: huge stocks of goods which have yet to be claimed back by their owners, Soeparto said. \par \par \uc2  Among the granted items are 18 luxury cars, such as Mercedes Benz, BMW and Nissan, he said. \par \par \uc2  "Like many of the other items, the cars are still in our East Jakarta office and are ready to be auctioned," he said, giving no further explanation. \par \par \uc2  The luxury cars belonged to people who desperate for cash, he explained. \par \par \uc2  Soeparto also said that his office had at least 80.25 kilograms of gold and about Rp 3 billion in various currencies which were all collected recently by the government in the nationwide Love Rupiah campaign. \par \par \uc2  He said his office kept the gold and the cash briefly before transferring it to \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 . (emf) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du2o008fi\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  House asks government to act on stabilizing the rupiah. \b0\par\par\uc2 487 \uc2 words\par \uc2 25 February 1998\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  (DPR) yesterday asked the government to take swift and clear action on the currency board system (CBS) or come up with alternative measures to stabilize the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  In a meeting between parliamentary factions and Finance Minister Mar'ie Muhammad here yesterday, the House also lend their support to CBS. \par \par \uc2  Separately, Bustanil Arifin, chairman of the APEC Business Advisory Council (ABAC), said that President Soeharto would like to see the rupiah pegged to the dollar as soon as possible. \par \par \uc2  Bustanil added that if the rupiah could be pegged at 5,000 to the dollar in April, the national \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could recover by July. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, a member of a state body tasked to stabilize the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Tanri Abeng, disclosed that the government has actually gone through the preparatory stage and is now in the stage of accelerating the implementation of CBS. \par \par \uc2  The ruling Golkar party's parliamentary faction's (FKP) spokesman Paskah Suzetta expressed her hope that the government would soon decide on whether or not to implement CBS and peg the rupiah to the dollar at 5,000 in accordance with IMF's proposal. \par \par \uc2  Sudirman, the spokesman of the military's faction (F-ABRI), also gave its support to CBS as it would provide "business and investment certainty". \par \par \uc2  The Moslem-backed faction F-PP also expressed its support to CBS "so long as the measure gives benefit and clear results to overcome the monetary crisis and restore \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  confidence in the rupiah." \par \par \uc2  F-PP is also convinced that CBS would put a halt on speculations which it blamed as the cause of the monetary turmoil. \par \par \uc2  The PDI House faction, F-PDI, also threw its weight behind CBS but warned that its implementation demands "strong discipline, which is still difficult to attain". \par \par \uc2  On the operational aspect of CBS, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  appears to be the body that is likely to be appointed by the government to implement it. \par \par \uc2  "As such, BI will not undergo much changes," said BI Governor Sjahril Sabirin yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, the rupiah strengthened by 75 points (0.9%) against the dollar amidst \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the CBS. \par \par \uc2  "\b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the CBS is increasingly being felt in the forex market. The factors are more political than \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  in nature," a broker in a European bank said as quoted by AP-Dow Jones. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah yesterday closed at 9,575 to the dollar in Jakarta's spot market, up from 9,650 on Monday. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, the US government announced that former Vice President Walter Mondale will leave for Jakarta on Saturday to convince President Soeharto the merits of adhering to the reforms proposed by IMF. \par \par \uc2  US President Bill Clinton decided to send Mondale to Indonesia as his personal representative after President Soeharto seems adamant in applying the CBS despite US pressure not to do so. (m2/ dj/psf/na/ab/ens/hl/p1). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010922du2p00095\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
