ight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis in decades, with the rupiah's value tumbling 70 percent against the U.S. dollar since last July. \par \par \uc2  Certain basic commodities, such as milk and cooking oil, have become scarce in supermarkets. Riots have broken out in several towns throughout the country with people burning stores they said hoarded goods. \par \par \uc2  Charges of hoarding essential goods carry penalties ranging from six years to death, officials have previously stated. They have said hoarders were to blame for soaring prices and shortages of basic items and could be charged with subversion, which could carry the death penalty. \par \par \uc2  Thirteen people have recently been detained by police on suspicion of hoarding. (das) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du2s007yo\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
