\par\par \b \uc2  Stocks, rupiah up on growing optimism. \b0\par\par\uc2 444 \uc2 words\par \uc2 14 March 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  9 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Stock prices on the Jakarta Stock Exchange (JSX) rose 1.7 percent yesterday on growing market speculation that the government would soon peg the rupiah to the U.S. dollar at a fixed rate, stockbrokers said. \par \par \uc2  They said the market also anticipated that the new cabinet ministers, to be announced by President Soeharto this morning, would soon give an impetus to solve the crisis. \par \par \uc2  After appointing the cabinet lineup, President Soeharto would likely introduce a fresh move early next week to mend the country's paralyzed \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , stockbrokers said. \par \par \uc2  "I think many people in the market are optimistic that the President will soon move to establishing the currency board system or just fixing the rupiah's rate against the dollar," a broker with a joint-venture securities said. \par \par \uc2  He said the market saw that the stalemate between the government and the International Monetary Fund over the former's plan to introduce a currency board would eventually ease after talks between Soeharto and visiting Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto this weekend. \par \par \uc2  Harita Securities president Christina Lim said stock prices improved because the market also expected that the new cabinet would soon give clear direction on how the government would deal with the crisis. \par \par \uc2  "Hopefully, we will see that direction very soon, after the announcement of the new cabinet ministers," she said. \par \par \uc2  Stockbrokers said trading activities remained moderate for the whole trading day yesterday though several foreign brokerage houses were making big buying orders on certain blue chips. \par \par \uc2  Brokers said leading foreign brokerages houses like Indosuez WICarr, Merrill Lynch, Jardine Fleming Nusantara, SBC Warburg, Credit Lyonnais were net buyers. \par \par \uc2  The JSX Composite index closed up 8.54 points to 506.73 yesterday from the previous day's 498.18. \par \par \uc2  Trading volume reached 468.65 million shares, changing hands on the regular market worth Rp 489.10 billion ($47.02 million). \par \par \uc2  Tracking the rise of stock prices, the rupiah strengthened slightly against the dollar in moderate transactions. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah closed at 10,400 against the dollar yesterday, up from the previous day's close of 10,500, currency dealers said. \par \par \uc2  "Nobody wants to make any transaction when the market remains \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  like this," a local bank chief dealer said. \par \par \uc2  He said most foreign operators, especially from Singapore, had squared their positions ahead of the weekend. \par \par \uc2  However, some operators were seen selling dollars, in the name of their clients who want to get rupiah to pay \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  next week. \par \par \uc2  Dealers said the composition of the new cabinet and the results of talks between Soeharto and Hashimoto would determine the fate of rupiah on Monday. (aly) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du3e008qv\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
