\par\par \b \uc2  Triple-tier project funding  \highlight22\uc2 uncertain \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 651 \uc2 words\par \uc2 2 April 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  3 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): City councilors urged the developer of the triple-tier transit system yesterday to reveal who will finance the Rp 6.2 trillion (US$730 million) project. \par \par \uc2  Helmy AR Syihab of the United Development Party faction said City Council should be informed of the sources of funds for the system, which would link Bintaro in South Jakarta to downtown Kota in West Jakarta \par \par \uc2  "It is important for the developer to explain where and how they will obtain the funds," he said. \par \par \uc2  Rusdji Hamka, one of the council's deputy chairmen, said an assurance that the developer could bankroll the mega-project was crucial. \par \par \uc2  "We still haven't been informed about the sources of funding during this time of (\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) crisis," he said. \par \par \uc2  "I'd say they'd be better off not trying to push ahead and complete the project during the crisis." \par \par \uc2  Helmy said the developer should also discuss the possibility of involving the city administration in the project by giving it an opportunity to own a share. \par \par \uc2  "Of course, the administration will not be able to buy its share in cash," he said. \par \par \uc2  "But I think the developer could let the administration have an interest to compensate for the city-owned land and properties to be used or demolished for the project." \par \par \uc2  Lukman Mokoginta of Commission D for \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  works, development and environmental affairs shared Helmy's view and insisted that the municipality have a stake in the project. \par \par \uc2  "The administration must be involved in the discussion and the calculation of the project together with the two state-owned companies Perumka and PT Jasa Marga which are involved in the joint venture," he said. \par \par \uc2  "It should know all about it, from the costs to the point it breaks even." \par \par \uc2  However, Lukman said the urgent completion of the project's environmental impact analysis (Amdal) by the developer was far more important than explaining its financial readiness. \par \par \uc2  "The developer is a private company. If it is confident that it has all the money needed to finance the project, then go ahead." \par \par \uc2  He said the sooner the project started, the better. \par \par \uc2  "The launch of the project during this time of crisis will help provide job opportunities for hundreds of people out there," Lukman, who represents the Indonesian Democratic Party faction, said. \par \par \uc2  "The developer must publish its Amdal because the people have a right to know exactly what the developer will build, what will happen to their land and what the costs and benefits of the project are." \par \par \uc2  Helmy said the developer had given hardly any information to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  regarding the project, which was scheduled to start operating in 2001. \par \par \uc2  "Many people still have no clear picture about the project, such as what it will be like or what areas will be used for it," he said. \par \par \uc2  "They don't know much about the project which will actually use the land on which their houses stand. \par \par \uc2  "Lack of information will just create chaos and resistance when the developer later asks people, whose land and properties will be affected by the project, to move away." \par \par \uc2  The triple-tier system will combine 23.65 kilometers of toll roads, 22 km of light-rail tracks and existing roads. \par \par \uc2  The project will be developed jointly by PT Citra Lamtoro Gung Persada, a company owned by Soeharto's eldest daughter who is also the Minister of Social Service, Siti Hardijanti Rukmana, the state-owned railway company Perumka and the state-owned highway corporation PT Jasa Marga under the company flag PT Citra Moda Margakencana Persada. \par \par \uc2  Helmy and Rusjdi said the City Council was still \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  whether the project would be continued as the developer had yet to provide further information on the groundbreaking ceremony. \par \par \uc2  The ceremony was postponed for the third time in February due to the city's preparations for the General Assembly in March. (cst) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du42009bc\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  BI mulls crawling band to stabilize rupiah. \b0\par\par\uc2 395 \uc2 words\par \uc2 2 April 1998\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) officials have indicated that the crawling band exchange rate has become an alternative in their efforts to stabilise the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  Miranda S. Goeltom, BI director, disclosed that the government is focusing discussions on monetary issues with regards to low-flexibility exchange rate systems. \par \par \uc2  Certainties in exchange rate developments would have greater benefits than allowing rates to fluctuate at the whim of market dynamics which "are not necessarily realistic." \par \par \uc2  "As such, a crawling band system would be better as it could provide guidelines on exchange rates to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Miranda said in her paper on exchange rates delivered in a seminar here yesterday. \par \par \uc2  The crawling band, Miranda explained, is an exchange rate regime alternative positioned between the fixed rate system and the flexible system. \par \par \uc2  Adjustments are made by depreciating the domestic exchange rate on the basis of inflation by continuously boosting the competitiveness of domestic products in the international market. \par \par \uc2  In contrast to the managed floating system which involves the intervention band [applied between 1986 and August 1997], the crawling band system does not recognise intervention. \par \par \uc2  In practice, the crawling band system permits BI to announce the rupiah's exchange rate at certain levels, for example 7,000/US$ or 8,000/US$, which, in accordance with prevailing situations, could be changed to different levels, low as well as high. \par \par \uc2  Rizal Ramli, Econit director, on the same occasion said that the government ought to abandon the free float system and revert to an exchange rate which is more fixed and pegged to the US$. \par \par \uc2  "The pegging system would provide certainties to the rupiah and would reduce the role of foreign anchors," he said. \par \par \uc2  The free floating system applied since 14 August last year has proven to be ineffective in sustaining external attacks, he added. \par \par \uc2  Miranda has meanwhile disclosed that the exchange rate system would be decided only after the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  has become stable. \par \par \uc2  "If we adjust a \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  under \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions, it is normally difficult to ascertain the results. But if the situation has become orderly, predicting results of a certain exchange rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could come close to our calculations," she said. \par \par \uc2  The government, Miranda added, prefers to see things on an overall basis, which is that the problem lies not solely in the exchange rate system. (m2/dj/ind/msw/ab). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010922du42000ut\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
