\par\par \b \uc2  Sales of industrial estates remain flat, analyst says. \b0\par\par\uc2 339 \uc2 words\par \uc2 4 April 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  6 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Sales of industrial estates in Bekasi, Karawang and Purwakarta in West Java remained flat in the first quarter of this year due to persistent \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the country's political and financial situation, a report says. \par \par \uc2  Property consultant PT First Pacific Davies Indonesia (FPDI) said the areas' industrial estates had few tenants in the January to March period. \par \par \uc2  The company, which recently conducted a survey on the industrial estates in the three locations, said estate sales had been much lower than in the first semester of last year. \par \par \uc2  "The four biggest industrial estates, with a combined area of 3,500 hectares, sold 110 hectares in the second semester of 1997, which is equivalent to 50 percent of the total sales for 1996," the company said. \par \par \uc2  The company said land prices at the industrial estates in the three cities remained stable at US$76 per square meter before \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  According to the property consultant, the sluggish sales were due to the fact that many prospective tenants were taking a "wait and see" attitude rather than signing contracts. \par \par \uc2  The company said these investors were concerned over the country's efforts to improve the ailing \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "Most investors questioned whether Indonesia would implement the International Monetary Fund's (IMF) \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform package or if the country would follow other measures to rescue its ailing \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," the report said of the prospective tenants asked. \par \par \uc2  The government and the IMF are currently working to amend the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform programs to heal the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Conclusion of the talks is expected to be announced later this week or early next week. \par \par \uc2  The property consultant firm also said the crisis affecting the region was also to blame for the stagnant industrial estate sales in the greater Jakarta area. \par \par \uc2  The company said 73 percent of the estates' established tenants were from Asia, while 18 percent were domestic, 1 percent were Australian, 3 percent were American and 5 percent were European. (aly) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du44009gl\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  IMF accord lifts BI-40. \b0\par\par\uc2 342 \uc2 words\par \uc2 9 April 1998\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Market players' waiting period has come to an end as the new RI-IMF accord, announced by Coordinating Minister of the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Finance Ginandjar Kartasasmita here yesterday, has now dispelled all \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the bourse. \par \par \uc2  Market players responded positively to the announcement by seeking blue chip shares with bright prospects. \par \par \uc2  The JSX index yesterday ended 3.895 points or 0.74% higher at 530.036, while the BI-40 index rose 0.963 point or 0.75% to 128.223. \par \par \uc2  The LQ45 index meanwhile went up 0.912 point to 117.79. \par \par \uc2  Following marathon meetings for three weeks, the government finally announced the results yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Five points have been added to a new memorandum, covering among others policies to stabilize the rupiah and rein in hyperinflation, improvement on the national banking system, \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies related to the impact of the rupiah's fall on the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , structural reforms to boost the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 's efficiency and the private foreign debt. \par \par \uc2  The government's strong commitment to implement the IMF-backed reform program IMF appeared to have encouraged investors to seek Bisnis prime shares. \par \par \uc2  Investors have high hopes that the government would seriously abide by IMF's demands which would in turn accelerate the process of Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  The government's plan to improve the legal system that would bolster competitive business and abolish all sorts of monopolies has also been received on a positive note by market players. \par \par \uc2  Share trading was buoyant in the morning but slackened in the afternoon as investors seemed to have become sceptic following government revisions over the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth and inflation rates. \par \par \uc2  For \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year 1998/99, the government has set the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth rate at -4% from its earlier figure of 0%, and inflation at 47%. \par \par \uc2  Oil price has also been revised to US$14.5 per barrel from US$17 barrel, while the current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been raised to 3.2% which officials say would be covered by foreign funds. (*). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010922du49000wq\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
