\par\par \b \uc2  Govt optimistic on rupiah value. \b0\par\par\uc2 579 \uc2 words\par \uc2 11 April 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The latest \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform package brokered by the International Monetary Fund (IMF) is expected to quickly strengthen the rupiah's exchange rate, according to an official document published yesterday. \par \par \uc2  The 20-point Supplementary Memorandum of \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Financial Policies - worked out jointly by the government and the IMF - does, however, predict soaring inflation and a contraction of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The rupiah's value should strengthen rapidly in the second quarter of 1998, it said. "We expect that the exchange rate will eventually stabilize below Rp 6,000 to the dollar." \par \par \uc2  Details of the package were released by Coordinating Minister of \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Finance and Industry Ginandjar Kartasasmita two days after the completion of the talks with the IMF. \par \par \uc2  The document, a revision to a 50-point Memorandum of Understanding signed by President Soeharto in January, culminates three weeks of intensive negotiations with the IMF, which has organized a US$43 billion rescue package for Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  While noting a continued deterioration, it hoped that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would begin to recover in the second half of this year. \par \par \uc2  Inflation could reach 45 percent in this calendar year, given that the consumer price index had already risen by 27 percent in the first quarter. But price increases have started to taper off, and inflation in the 1998/1999 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year should slow down to between 17 and 20 percent, it said. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is also predicted to contract by 5 percent in the calendar year 1998 and 4 percent in \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  1998/1999. \par \par \uc2  In a brief statement yesterday, Ginandjar cautioned against overoptimism on inflation and growth projections. "The degree of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  remains high. These assumptions could still change." \par \par \uc2  Officials and analysts agree that restoring the rupiah's exchange rate is a crucial precondition to any recovery. The rupiah has plunged from Rp 2,400 to the dollar in July last year to Rp 17,000 in January. On Thursday, it traded at about Rp 7,800. \par \par \uc2  The government hopes to stabilize the rupiah's exchange rate by tightening its monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , specifically curtailing \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  liquidity credits to commercial banks through setting high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  on \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  promissory notes (SBIs). \par \par \uc2  The latest \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform package promises the enactment of an antimonopoly law, a new bankruptcy law, the establishment of a special bankruptcy court and the introduction of regulations for the winding up of companies, mergers and acquisitions. \par \par \uc2  It also calls for an end to the palm oil export ban, replacing it with a \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  of not more than 40 percent. \par \par \uc2  It outlines a program for privatization of state enterprises and for accelerated restructuring of the battered banking sector. \par \par \uc2  The package also provides a framework to resolve the $74 billion in corporate foreign debt. \par \par \uc2  The debt issue, despite its contribution to the crisis, was not specifically addressed in the January package, a factor that led to the rupiah plunging even further in the days immediately after it was announced. \par \par \uc2  The latest reform package revised some of the assumptions used in calculating the government \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  this \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year, which is now expected to register a \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  equal to 3.2 percent of the gross domestic product. \par \par \uc2  The package commits the government to phase out \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  on food - except for rice and soybeans - and on medicines, energy and fuels. It sets an October deadline for the termination of all \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 , except for fuels. (rei/emb) \par \par \uc2  Related stories on Page 6 \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du4b0099u\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
