\par\par \b \uc2  MARKET REPORT - Concerns over reform drag down rupiah again. \b0\par\par\uc2 375 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 April 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  6 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The crippled rupiah fell for the second consecutive day yesterday on market apprehension over the country's commitment to thoroughly implementing the revised reforms, currency dealers said. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah, which opened at 7,700/7,800, closed 2.6 percent lower than the previous day's close of 7,650 against the American dollar, they said. \par \par \uc2  "The market has sensed a kind of signal from the government that it might backtrack on the reform program agreed with the International Monetary Fund," a currency dealer with a local private bank said. \par \par \uc2  Mounting concerns arose Tuesday following a controversial remark by Minister of Industry and Trade Mohamad "Bob" Hasan that Indonesia would not honor its IMF commitment to revoke a crude palm oil export ban by April 22, the dealer said. \par \par \uc2  "Any controversial comments like that only send a very bad message to foreign investors, prompting them to keep dumping the rupiah." \par \par \uc2  The chief IMF representative in Jakarta, Kadhim Al-Eyd, said yesterday that he had been assured by Bob Hasan that the ban would be scrapped according to the deadline. \par \par \uc2  Currency dealers said that students staging demonstration on their campuses across the country, demanding \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political reform, had also prompted most foreign operators to remain on the sidelines of the market. \par \par \uc2  "Overseas investors perceive the country's political risk as being still high," another local bank dealer said. \par \par \uc2  Dealers said \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the resolution of the country's foreign debts in New York had also put more pressure on the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  They said market concern about the failure of an expected rise in \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to materialize also contributed to the rupiah's slide yesterday. \par \par \uc2  As the rupiah fell, stock prices on the Jakarta Stock Exchange (JSX) also declined as most investors stayed on the sidelines to watch closely the implementation of the reform program. \par \par \uc2  Stock analysts said a weakening regional market was also responsible for a downturn on the JSX. \par \par \uc2  The JSX Composite Index closed 2.65 points lower to 513.44 points on total volume of 431.18 million shares changing hands on the regular market valued at Rp 666.94 billion (US$85.50 million). (aly) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du4g009j3\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  CGI members undecided over aid to RI. \b0\par\par\uc2 449 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 April 1998\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Donor countries grouped under the CGI [Consultative Group for Indonesia] have yet to decide its stance on aid and loans to Indonesia which would be determined at its meeting in Paris on July. \par \par \uc2  World Bank chief representative Dennis de Tray said that the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation has greatly changed in a way that has made CGI members to wait and see the results of the government's efforts to implement reforms and deal with the current crisis. \par \par \uc2  "We plan to hold the CGI meeting in July in Paris and see a constructive discussion on Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stabilization program," De Tray told Bisnis yesterday after a meeting with NGOs here in Jakarta. \par \par \uc2  The World Bank is an important multilateral contributor in CGI after the ADB, while the largest bilateral donor is Japan. \par \par \uc2  The CGI last year in Tokyo committed loans amounting to US$5.29 billion, of which the World Bank provided US$1.5 billion, ADB US$1.2 billion and the Islamic Development Bank US$100 million, bringing total multilateral commitment to US$3.036 billion. \par \par \uc2  Bilateral commitment reached US$2.262 billion with Japan setting aside US$1.869 billion, the US with US$74 million, and South Korea US$72,6 million. \par \par \uc2  De Tray refused to give his estimates when asked whether the World Bank would come up with a same amount of commitment this year, saying it is "a sensitive matter." \par \par \uc2  "The amount depends on how we perceive Indonesia's present conditions and prospects," he said. \par \par \uc2  De Tray went on to say that the government ought to come up with an affirmative program that is "transparent, credible and open" so that it would benefit many people. \par \par \uc2  The World Bank as a matter of routine would issue an annual report on Indonesia on the eve of the CGI meeting. \par \par \uc2  The report, De Tray said, is still being prepared because of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis and the basic changes that have beset the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis and the changes that came with it in the past six months, including the prospects of the capital market and other \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  aspects, are being studied carefully as prospective means to stabilize the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , he said. \par \par \uc2  Many parties, he said, are discussing Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  basics which they say are very weak and fraught with \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Bilateral and multilateral loans and aids to Indonesia have reached about US$5 billion every year. \par \par \uc2  Multilateral commitment has in the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year of 1995/96 rose from US$2.565 billion to US$2.671 billion in 1996/97 and US$3.036 billion in 1997/98. (04/ab/her). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010922du4i000yy\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Astra Otoparts to offer 75m shares to  \highlight22\uc2 public \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 411 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 April 1998\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  PT Astra Otoparts, a unit of PT Astra International, plans a \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  offering (IPO) of 75 millions shares expected to be worth Rp40 billion to Rp45 billion. \par \par \uc2  Yannes Naibaho, president and chief executive officer of PT Usaha Bersama Securities, the lead underwriter for Astra Otoparts, said the shares to be offered to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 , with a par value of Rp500 per share, amount to 10% of the company's after IPO-paid up capital. \par \par \uc2  Naibaho said 50% of the funds from IPO will be used to recapitalize the company, 30% to repay short-term loans and 20% for operation \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "I am optimistic that the market will absorb the shares. Hopefully the shares will be oversubscribed," he said after a pre-IPO press conference on Friday. \par \par \uc2  Despite an \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , he said, Astra Otoparts is confident in the success of the IPO because the company does not offer a big amount of shares. The par value of the shares is also set a discount rate, he said. \par \par \uc2  "I think offering 10 percent of shares is realistic under the current circumstances," he added. \par \par \uc2  Company director Benny Redjo Setyono said he estimates a 32.76% increase in sales to Rp1.1 trillion, up from Rp828.572 billion last year. He attributed the sales increase to a planned increase of the company product prices between 21% and 80%. \par \par \uc2  Even so, he said, net profit is expected to decline 65.99% this year to Rp14 billion, from Rp41.165 billion last year due to foreign exchange losses. \par \par \uc2  "In 1997, we faced foreign exchange losses and swap premiums of Rp61 billion, almost 10 times of that in 1996," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said earning projection for this year is based on assumption of a rupiah exchange rate at Rp9,000 to the dollar in the first quarter, Rp7,000 in the second quarter and Rp6,000 in the third quarter. \par \par \uc2  Until December 1997, the company faced a consolidated foreign exchange of US$94.5 million, of which 70% were hedged at an exchange rate of Rp2,700 to the dollar. \par \par \uc2  The exchange rate losses of the remaining 30% that stayed unhedged amounted to Rp60.1 billion, all was registered for the 1997 financial balance sheet. \par \par \uc2  Based on a consolidated balance, the company's total debt amounts to Rp829.281 billion, comprising of Rp468.023 short-term loans and Rp340.258 long-term loans. \par \par \uc2  (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010922du4i000z7\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
