\par\par \b \uc2  Road to  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  recovery full of potholes. \b0\par\par\uc2 799 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 April 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Government officials have made confusing statements on the reforms sponsored by the International Monetary Fund (IMF). Economist Sri Mulyani Indrawati, vice chairwoman of the University of Indonesia's Center for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Social Studies, discusses the government's commitment to the measures. \par \par \uc2  Question: Do you think the government will again backtrack on the implementation of the IMF-sponsored \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform? \par \par \uc2  Mulyani: I am afraid the issuance of confusing statements was due to \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  ministers' poor sense of belonging and lack of comprehensive understanding of the reform measures, which are vast in coverage. The measures are actually so detailed, explicit and demanding that it is almost impossible for Indonesia to backtrack. \par \par \uc2  Q: Do you see any parties opposing the reform? \par \par \uc2  M: There are... they will surely try to make deviations in its implementation. The key problem is that relations between powerholders and business circles have been too close. Those who want to strictly enforce the reform measures will have to create adequate distance between the two. Transparency and fair competition in business activities cannot be established within just one or two months... However, reforms are a good initial action which, coupled with \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  pressures, will encourage government officials to stop using power to benefit their own business interests. \par \par \uc2  Q: Will intensification of student demonstrations affect the business environment? \par \par \uc2  M: They will, at least, be a pressure point for the government to become aware that signing an IMF reform agreement is not enough as society, represented by university students, is demanding establishment of a modern, consistent and transparent \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  system in the country. Such an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  system, in line with IMF reform measures, is also awaited by foreign investors. Their return will depend on how the government manages the whole dynamics of the society and the momentum for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  Q: Now that the government has been implementing the IMF reforms, do you see it winning \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  trust? \par \par \uc2  M: Cabinet members involved in last weekend's dialog meeting with students tried to show they were working hard to overcome the... crisis, but there is skepticism in society on whether the government has done its best... in line with what they want. \par \par \uc2  Such skepticism, caused by a bad image of the government, will undermine effectiveness of any policies it introduces. The government must therefore eradicate this image and try to manage society so it will behave in line with reform policies. If the government ignores this, the policies will not be effective. \par \par \uc2  Q: The government has apparently revised its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  for the second time, although it has yet to be announced... \par \par \uc2  M: Starting this \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year, the government is required to substantially change its budgetary policies because its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  will have extraordinarily heavy burdens ... it now has to bear costs of the issuance of government bonds, the restructuring of the banking industry, the solution of private corporation debt problems and social safety-net programs. \par \par \uc2  It actually has to explain this new \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which is not explicitly mentioned in the IMF reform, to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 , who is participating in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  through its \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  payments. \par \par \uc2  In future, the government will probably also have to revise its balanced \b \highlight22\uc2 budget policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  due to changes in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions. \par \par \uc2  Q: What about prospects for the rupiah's conversion rate? \par \par \uc2  M: I think a target of a conversion rate of Rp 6,000 per U.S. dollar will be reachable by the end of the 1998/1999 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year next March on the condition that the IMF reform measures are implemented as scheduled. However, \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  may affect the conversion rate's development because implementation of the full reform measures cannot guarantee the achievement of the target. \par \par \uc2  Facts show implementation of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms and the situation of dollar supply and demand contribute only about 70 percent to the exchange rate development ... (the rest) is determined by the subjective perceptions of market players. \par \par \uc2  The government must manage the situation so market players will behave positively toward implementation of the reforms. \par \par \uc2  Q: Depositors are worried about savings in commercial banks. Do you expect the banking industry will improve under the supervision of the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA)? \par \par \uc2  M: It is difficult to expect the banking industry to recover its flawed intermediary function. \par \par \uc2  (Because of this) ...\b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , has decided to begin this week to offer its promissory notes, SBIs, directly to individual depositors in its effort to contract the money supply within a short period of time. \par \par \uc2  The IBRA will probably need two years to have commercial banks recover their intermediary function... it is also required to make management at individual commercial banks more transparent to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  because it has involved \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  funds, in the form of bonds, in their financial restructuring. (riz) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du4m009rl\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
