\par\par \b \uc2  Postpone sticker plan until crisis end - Golkar. \b0\par\par\uc2 579 \uc2 words\par \uc2 25 April 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  3 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The Golkar faction in the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  added yesterday to mounting pressure on the city administration to shelve plans to introduce a traffic sticker system. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, the Jakarta Legal Aid Institute (LBH) demanded that President Soeharto rescind the decree he issued earlier this month which endorsed the controversial plan. \par \par \uc2  Golkar faction chief Irsyad Sudiro suggested that Governor Sutiyoso postpone the scheme, which is scheduled to be tested between August and November, until the crippling \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis comes to an end. \par \par \uc2  "It would be inappropriate to further burden people who are already weighted down by the crisis," he said. "Remember, not all motorists entering the restricted zone are rich." \par \par \uc2  Plans to introduce the controversial system were put into motion following Presidential Decree No. 50, 1998, on the restricted traffic area in the city, and the 1998 Government \b \highlight22\uc2 Regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  No. 45 on regional levies. \par \par \uc2  The sticker system would require people wanting to travel along Jl. M.H. Thamrin and Jl. Jend. Sudirman between 7:30 a.m. and 9:30 a.m., and between 5 p.m. and 7 p.m. on week days to pay Rp 5,000 (60 U.S. cents) for a one-day entry sticker, or Rp 80,000 for a one month pass. \par \par \uc2  The system is intended to help alleviate chronic traffic congestion in the city center and will replace the current three-in-one traffic \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  which was introduced in 1992. \par \par \uc2  The three-in-one system, which requires private cars entering the restricted zone at peak times to contain at least three people, is considered to have been ineffective in dealing with the city's traffic problem. \par \par \uc2  Irsyad said the city administration's determination to press on with the new system despite strong \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  objections showed that the governor was \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  about how best to deal with traffic congestion in Jakarta. \par \par \uc2  Minister of Communications Giri Suseno Hadihardjono should explain the plan to the House and guarantee its effectiveness, he said. \par \par \uc2  "If it's only designed to collect money, the plan should be scrapped because not all motorists can afford to buy the stickers," he said, as quoted by Antara. \par \par \uc2  Giri proposed on Wednesday that Sutiyoso consider a compromise solution where only cars carrying less than three people have to buy a sticker. \par \par \uc2  Both Golkar and the institute agree that the administration is prevented by law from collecting levies on non-toll roads like Jl. Thamrin and Jl. Sudirman. \par \par \uc2  On a separate occasion, the institute's Jakarta director Apong Herlina proposed that President Soeharto revoke his decree because the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  was strongly opposed to the sticker system. \par \par \uc2  Besides, she said, the laws on which the President based his decree were designed to regulate the city administration's income generating activities, not to deal with traffic congestion. \par \par \uc2  Apong argued that requiring motorists to purchase stickers to enter the city center was tantamount to charging levies on a non-toll road, a practice which is clearly illegal under the provisions of Law No. 14, 1992,on traffic and land transportation. \par \par \uc2  "The law stipulates that everybody can use roads free of charge unless the roads are designated toll roads," she said. \par \par \uc2  "The President should therefore rescind his decree out of respect for the law." \par \par \uc2  The institute plans to ask the Supreme Court to conduct a judicial review of the disputed Presidential decree and rule on whether or not it contradicts the existing law. (ind) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du4p009uh\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  S&P revises Bank Exim rating to CCCpi. \b0\par\par\uc2 233 \uc2 words\par \uc2 25 April 1998\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Rating agency Standard & Poor's has revised the rating of PT Bank EksporImpor Indonesia (Exim) from N.M. (not meaningful) to CCCp1 following the bank's release from the supervision of the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA). \par \par \uc2  S&P said in a release that the decision is based on a Finance Minister Fuad Bawazier's statement that the government plans inject fresh capital into Bank Exim. \par \par \uc2  S&P said the CCCpi rating reflected concerns about the potential impact on Bank Exim's asset quality from a rise in borrower defaults following a serious deterioration in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Bank Exim had been rated N.M. following IBRA's decision to place the bank under its supervision. The rating indicated a situation of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  of the company's future financial performance. \par \par \uc2  When asked to comment, a number of House members warned that government's capital injection to Bank Exim requires approval from the House of People Representative (DPR). "The capital injection plan has to be put in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," said Hamzah Haz of the United Development Party faction. \par \par \uc2  Budi Hardjono, a House member of the Indonesian Democratic Party faction, said he has for number of times reminded the government that any transfer of state assets have to be discussed at DPR including 