\par\par \b \uc2  Business tremors may make L/C guarantee futile. \b0\par\par\uc2 574 \uc2 words\par \uc2 9 May 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Drained confidence in the domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and business sector may undermine the workability of the billion-dollar letter of credit guarantee available from the country's major trading partners, importers said yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Chairman of the Indonesian Importers Association (GINSI), Amirudin Saud, said local banks were demanding that importers provide 100 percent cash up-front as a security deposit to open a L/C because of the teetering \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "This is difficult to fulfill because of the tight liquidity environment," he told The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2  In tandem with the country's monetary crisis which started in July last year, overseas banks have rejected local L/Cs due to depleted confidence in the ailing domestic bank sector. \par \par \uc2  The problem has crippled the country's production system, which needs up to 50 percent of imported materials, including the export industry. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia's major donor countries have agreed to provide multibillion credit facilities to guarantee the country's imports following the International Monetary Fund's (IMF) agreement to disburse the second tranche of its pledged bailout loan. \par \par \uc2  Amirudin said L/Cs issued by Indonesian banks would face no more rejections because they would be covered by the credit insurance. \par \par \uc2  Several importers, however, said there was another obstacle to the workability of the L/C guarantee. \par \par \uc2  "This time, the difficulty comes from local banks, not overseas banks," a businessman said. \par \par \uc2  Local banks required importers to put 100 percent cash up-front to open their L/C, he said, adding that the deposit security was needed because banks doubted the viability of local corporates due to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. \par \par \uc2  Describing the "current high interest environment", he said that putting a 100 percent security deposit to guarantee the L/C would be extremely expensive. \par \par \uc2  "If we have such a large fund, we may prefer to place it in the deposit, which now offers very attractive rates." \par \par \uc2  He said banks could be reluctant to provide credit for the up-front cash because they preferred to put their cash in less risky \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  promissory notes. \par \par \uc2  BI raised the \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  of its short-term promissory notes (SBIs) on Thursday, boosting the rate of the one-month SBIs to 58 percent from 50 percent. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  has resurfaced following this week's student demonstrations demanding political reform which descended into riots in Medan, North Sumatra. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah fell back to as low as Rp 10,000 to the U.S. dollar after it managed to rise to about Rp 8,000 following the government's expressed commitment to follow the IMF-sponsored \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform programs, and a rise in BI's benchmark \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  last month. \par \par \uc2  Amirudin said that the increasing volatility of the rupiah had also raised the cost of opening a L/C as the up-front dollar deposit would be based on a high exchange rate. \par \par \uc2  He also said that even though the overseas credit financing had been disbursed, not all local corporates were eligible for the facilities because foreign banks would only accept L/Cs drawn up by local companies which had not exploited preferential government treatment. \par \par \uc2  "Those which made businesses on government special favors will be rejected by the foreign banks," he said. He cited the rejection experienced by particular importers even though BI had put a total of $1 billion in overseas banks to guarantee local L/Cs. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du5900a89\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Ginandjar - RI  \highlight22\uc2 economy \highlight\uc2  can recover sooner. \b0\par\par\uc2 197 \uc2 words\par \uc2 9 May 1998\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Coordinating Minister of the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Finance Ginandjar Kartasasmita has said that Indonesia would be able to recover its \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  sooner at a growth rate of 6%-7% if political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  was not a factor in its IMF US$43 billion-assisted \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery programs. \par \par \uc2  Ginandjar, in an interview with Dow Jones here yesterday, said that Indonesia would experience at least two years of negative \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth but is set to rise again in the year 2000 if the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform programs are successful. \par \par \uc2  "If all ongoing reform programs can be implemented without a hitch, we will have stabilized by next year," he predicted. \par \par \uc2  He said the next two years that end on 31 March, 2000 would be "\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stabilization years". \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , he said, is estimated to grow by -5% during the current \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year - as agreed in the supplementary memorandum - and grow by 0% in the following year [1999/2000]. \par \par \uc2  Earlier, economist Rizal Ramli of Ekonit said that \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery could only happen if a new political equilibrium is reached among those involved in the bargaining process that is now taking place in society. (ab). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010922du590015r\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
